challenge.prompt:
The classic pre-C++26 way to get the N-th element of a pack is a recursive helper. Rewrite it as a one-liner using pack indexing.

```cpp
template <std::size_t N, typename T0, typename... Ts>
auto nth(T0 t0, Ts... ts) {
    if constexpr (N == 0) return t0; else return nth<N - 1>(ts...);
}
```

